Re: We accept Bitcoins

Bitcointalk

2010-05-20 21:43:42 UTC - [11]Original Post

   [12]Quote from: DataWraith on May 19, 2010, 07:52:42 PM
   Can I just butt in with a question on why that is? To me it seems that
   if Bitcoin uses public-key cryptography to transfer ownership of the
   coins, it should be a trivial matter to include a short message that is
   only readable by the recipient.
   Almost but not quite.  Bitcoin uses EC-DSA, which can only do digital
   signing, not encryption.  RSA can do both, but I didnʼt use it because
   itʼs an order of magnitude bigger and would have been impractical.
